Texts.Chs: 克里昂真是个迷人的城市！
Texts.Eng: Creon is a fascinating city.

Texts.Chs: 别进下水道,你很容易在那里面晕头转向。
Texts.Eng: Do not go into the sewers. You can easily get lost in there.

Texts.Chs: 你明白生命的意义吗？
Texts.Eng: Do you know the meaning of life?

Texts.Chs: 您常来这里吗？舰长？
Texts.Eng: Do you visit here often?

Texts.Chs: 你好，旅行者。
Texts.Eng: Greetings, traveler.

Texts.Chs: 你好。
Texts.Eng: Greetings.

Texts.Chs: 您去过雏机人的大使馆吗？
Texts.Eng: Have you been to the Trinkian embassy yet?

Texts.Chs: 去过招募办公室吗？ 在那儿你能轻松找到更多雇员。
Texts.Eng: Have you been to the recruitment office yet? You can easily find more crewmembers there.

Texts.Chs: 大使馆的最高层你去没去过？ 那里有一扇锁着的门，我好想知道它的背后是什么。
Texts.Eng: Have you been to the top level of the embassy? There's a locked door there. I wonder what's behind it?

Texts.Chs: 您去过联邦建立的其中一个殖民地吗？ 对它印象如何？
Texts.Eng: Have you ever been to one of the Union colonies? What was it like?

Texts.Chs: 试过搭便车没？ 那可甚是有趣。
Texts.Eng: Have you ever tried hitchhiking? It's great fun.

Texts.Chs: 哈啊...？哦！你好呀！
Texts.Eng: Huh? Oh, hi there!

Texts.Chs: 草，我车呢？！ 希望咱不会像上次那样给它忘在屋顶上……
Texts.Eng: I forgot where I parked my hovercar again. Hope I didn't leave it on a roof like last time...

Texts.Chs: 我曾狠狠挨了某匹凯尔贝特一记头槌，那小可怜把自己伤得不轻。
Texts.Eng: I got head-butted by one of the Kelbet once. Poor thing hurt itself quite badly.

Texts.Chs: 爷有张能进入使馆地下靶场的绿卡。 不，你别想拿到它，别想。
Texts.Eng: I have a pass to enter the embassy gun range. No, you can't have it.

Texts.Chs: 我听闻有些可怖的事降临在了地球上...
Texts.Eng: I heard something awful happened to Earth.

Texts.Chs: 最近我听到小镇的下水井里发出了些奇怪的噪音。 也许我该把这事报告给P-ASA ...
Texts.Eng: I heard strange noises in the sewers below the town. Maybe I should report them to P-ASA...

Texts.Chs: 我听说他们有计划进一步扩大使馆。 我很好奇，接下来还会添加什么。
Texts.Eng: I heard there are plans to expand the embassy even further. I am curious to see what will be added next.

Texts.Chs: 我听别人说下水道里有个雏机，名叫“螺栓”。 这事儿听起来有点假。
Texts.Eng: I heard there's a Trink in the sewers by the name of 'the Bolter'. Sounds sketchy.

Texts.Chs: 我帮助设计了使馆的能源电网。它可是非常有效。
Texts.Eng: I helped design the embassy's power grid. It is very efficient.

Texts.Chs: 我就在这里搭个便车。
Texts.Eng: I hitchhiked my way here.

Texts.Chs: 希望大使馆里的那些阿威坎们不是来这里猎杀机器人的...
Texts.Eng: I hope that Avikan in the embassy isn't here to hunt down machines...

Texts.Chs: 我在某个地方落了钥匙。 也许还是去趟失物招领处比较有用。
Texts.Eng: I lost my keys somewhere. Perhaps the lost and found booth can help me.

Texts.Chs: 我喜欢看到夜晚的城市灯光亮起来。
Texts.Eng: I love seeing the city lights turn on at night.

Texts.Chs: 我喜爱那些使馆观景池里的鱼。
Texts.Eng: I love the fish in the embassy's pools.

Texts.Chs: 我爱以利提亚的那些星球模型。 它们令我感到渺小。
Texts.Eng: I love those globes of Elithia. Makes me feel small.

Texts.Chs: 我最近刚毕业！
Texts.Eng: I recently graduated!

Texts.Chs: 我看到有些士兵在使馆塔楼上。 有些担忧他们为什么会在那里？
Texts.Eng: I saw soldiers way up in the embassy tower. I wonder why they're there?

Texts.Chs: 我见过塔顶的那箱子。 不知里面会有些什么？
Texts.Eng: I saw this chest way up on the tower. I wonder what's in it?

Texts.Chs: 我在大使馆里见过这个怪异的外星人，我猜是个阿基马里人，一想就让我浑身难受。
Texts.Eng: I saw this strange alien in the embassy, an Akkimari I think. Made me feel uneasy.

Texts.Chs: 我觉得我在城镇附近的那些悬崖之上看到了某些东西。
Texts.Eng: I think I saw something up on those cliffs near the town.

Texts.Chs: 我试驾过一次安怡突击舰，不怎么适合我开。
Texts.Eng: I tried to enter an Aventor Galliot once. I didn't quite fit.

Texts.Chs: 我曾是个和你一样的旅行者，但我已经厌了。
Texts.Eng: I used to be a traveler like you, but I got bored of that life.

Texts.Chs: 我想要一只转基犬。
Texts.Eng: I want a Trangii.

Texts.Chs: 我想回家打电动啊。
Texts.Eng: I want to go home and play some games.

Texts.Chs: 好想有一天能去西西旅行哪。
Texts.Eng: I want to visit Scii some day.

Texts.Chs: 总有一天我会去拜访那些殖民地的。
Texts.Eng: I want to visit the colonies one day.

Texts.Chs: 我希望能住进大城市。
Texts.Eng: I wish I lived in the big city.

Texts.Chs: 我多希望我也是大使啊。 我将要去的地方会是...
Texts.Eng: I wish I was an ambassador too. The places I'd get to visit...

Texts.Chs: 不知道远处的那座塔究竟有多高？
Texts.Eng: I wonder how high that tower in the distance really is?

Texts.Chs: 那些下水道为啥禁止入内？
Texts.Eng: I wonder why the sewers are off-limits?

Texts.Chs: 咱真心为使馆里有这么多卫生间而感到庆幸。
Texts.Eng: I'm glad the embassy has plenty of public toilets.

Texts.Chs: 我曾经在城镇下面的窨井里呆过。 那里稍微有点吓人。
Texts.Eng: I've been inside the sewers beneath the town once. It's kinda scary in there.

Texts.Chs: 我在那座大城市里有房子。 您实际上都能从这儿看到它。
Texts.Eng: I've got a home in the big city. You can actually see it from here.

Texts.Chs: 天啊！我听说过你！ 您就是<entityname>, 对吧？
Texts.Eng: I've heard of you! You are <entityname>, right?

Texts.Chs: 我在这里见过一些怪人。 可把我吓坏了。
Texts.Eng: I've seen some weird people here. I was kinda freaked out.

Texts.Chs: 这是您第一次来访以利提亚吗？
Texts.Eng: Is this your first time visiting Elithia?

Texts.Chs: 这个地方不是很好吗？ 它拥有一切我需要的东西！
Texts.Eng: Isn't this place great? It's got everything I'd ever need!

Texts.Chs: 欣赏着树木在埃癸建筑群的顶部茁壮生长，可真是令人着迷。 这是对空间的非常有效的利用。
Texts.Eng: It is fascinating to see the trees growing on top of Aeginian buildings. It's a very efficient use of space.

Texts.Chs: 很高兴看到，同志们更加依赖公共线路而不是个人交通。 这样效率很高。
Texts.Eng: It is good to see that the Aegi rely more on public transportation than personal transportation. It's quite efficient.

Texts.Chs: 在这里能看到如此多的野生动物真是特别。 他们并不怎么害怕我们。
Texts.Eng: It is odd to see so much wildlife here. They are not exactly afraid of us.

Texts.Chs: 使馆的许多灯光只在晚上打开。 我很欣赏这套系统的效能。
Texts.Eng: Many of the embassy's lights only turn on at night. I like the efficiency of the system.

Texts.Chs: 我表弟前几天换了台新的安怡突击舰（Aventor Galliot）。 说实话我有点酸。
Texts.Eng: My cousin got a new Aventor Galliot the other day. I'm a bit jealous.

Texts.Chs: 我的花粉症又犯了。
Texts.Eng: My hayfever is acting up again.

Texts.Chs: 我的宠物转基犬应该就在这附近某处吧。
Texts.Eng: My pet Trangii should be around here somewhere.

Texts.Chs: 早些时候那些转基犬中的一只凶了我，它可能不喜欢我。
Texts.Eng: One of those Trangii barked at me earlier. I don't think it likes me.

Texts.Chs: 看着远处的都市总能令我感到开心。
Texts.Eng: Seeing the city in the distance always makes me feel happy.

Texts.Chs: 埃癸人同志们都是·热狍·（Hötbrod）的铁粉，但我真的get不到点。
Texts.Eng: The Aegi are big fans of Hötbrod, but I don't really get the fascination.

Texts.Chs: 克里昂大使馆的确有些好东西，对吧？ 这是一个很棒的打卡地。
Texts.Eng: The Creon Embassy is really something, huh? It's such a great place to visit.

Texts.Chs: 克里昂大使馆是如此一座宏伟的建筑。
Texts.Eng: The Creon Embassy is such a large building.

Texts.Chs: 克里昂使馆也许不是最大的使馆，但它却位列最好的使馆之中。
Texts.Eng: The Creon Embassy may not be the largest embassy, but it is one of the best.

Texts.Chs: 这里的凯尔贝特们真是娴雅。
Texts.Eng: The Kelbet here are so peaceful.

Texts.Chs: 这里的P-ASA干员们非常警惕。
Texts.Eng: The P-ASA officers here are very vigilant.

Texts.Chs: 使馆的横幅真是太酷了。 能使所有人都感到彼此相连。
Texts.Eng: The banners in the embassy are so cool. Makes us all feel connected.

Texts.Chs: 镇上的书店虽小，但真的很赞。
Texts.Eng: The bookstore in town is small, but pretty good.

Texts.Chs: 这里的气候真的舒服。 连雨都还算不错。
Texts.Eng: The climate here is really comfortable. Even the rain isn't too bad.

Texts.Chs: 大使馆的电梯运转效率很高。
Texts.Eng: The elevators in the embassy run very efficiently.

Texts.Chs: 使馆内部实际备有枪支测试场。 您需要特殊的通行证才能访问它。
Texts.Eng: The embassy actually has a gun range. You need a special pass to access it though.

Texts.Chs: 大使馆总是会提供与盟军星网的卓越连接。
Texts.Eng: The embassy always offers exceptional connection to the Allied Interstellar Network.

Texts.Chs: 这里的花园真漂亮。
Texts.Eng: The gardens here are so pretty.

Texts.Chs: 使馆接待处的那位女士帮助我良多。
Texts.Eng: The lady at the embassy's reception desk was actually quite helpful to me.

Texts.Chs: 这里的这座公园令人难以置信地安静平和。
Texts.Eng: The parks here are incredibly peaceful.

Texts.Chs: 该镇上有一些很不错的商店，但大多数于我都没什么用。
Texts.Eng: The town has some good shops in it, but most of it isn't very relevant to me.

Texts.Chs: 该镇的正式官方名称为使馆村。 它实际上不是克里昂的一部分，但恰好就在它的边缘。
Texts.Eng: The town is officially called the Embassy Village. It's not actually part of Creon, but it's right on the edge.

Texts.Chs: 镇上的汽车经销店有一些很棒的载具可供出售。
Texts.Eng: The vehicle dealership in the town has some great rides for sale.

Texts.Chs: 使馆机库中有很多雏机工程师。 很高兴在这里看到更多我的同类。
Texts.Eng: There are many Trinkian engineers in the embassy hangars. It's good to see more of my kind here.

Texts.Chs: 大使馆更高的楼层里有一位联邦上将。 我还没有获得与他交流的许可。
Texts.Eng: There is a Union Admiral in the embassy's upper levels. I haven't been allowed to speak to him yet.

Texts.Chs: 使馆机库里有个技工可以修理损坏的载具。
Texts.Eng: There's a mechanic in the embassy's hangars who fixes up broken vehicles.

Texts.Chs: 镇上有一家商店出售海报。 我想要NSI的海报，但是有点贵。
Texts.Eng: There's a shop in the town that sells posters. I wanted the NSI poster, but it's kinda expensive.

Texts.Chs: 镇上有一家很棒的礼品店。
Texts.Eng: There's an awesome gift shop in the town.

Texts.Chs: 这里有各“种”各样的人。
Texts.Eng: There's people of all kinds of species here.

Texts.Chs: 使馆里有那么多的电梯！
Texts.Eng: There's so many elevators in the embassy.

Texts.Chs: 使馆的机库里有一些极好的雏机工程师和机械师。
Texts.Eng: There's some great Trinkian engineers and mechanics in the embassy's hangar.

Texts.Chs: 大使馆里有那样一位阿威坎友人，我期望他们什么时候也能加入联盟。
Texts.Eng: There's this one Avikan fellow in the embassy. I hope they join the Alliance at some point, too.

Texts.Chs: 该使馆是以利提亚联盟的一个极佳的代表象征。
Texts.Eng: This embassy is a good representation of the Elithian Alliance.

Texts.Chs: 这个地方很迷人。
Texts.Eng: This place is quite fascinating.

Texts.Chs: 想去喝一杯吗？
Texts.Eng: Wanna go grab a drink?

Texts.Chs: 想和我一起去看看·热狍·小摊吗？
Texts.Eng: Want to come with me and visit the Hötbrod stand?

Texts.Chs: 舒缓地看着远处悬浮车辆川流不息是如此抚慰人心。
Texts.Eng: Watching the hovercars in the distance is so soothing.

Texts.Chs: 哟，今个又是什么风儿把您给吹来大使馆了？
Texts.Eng: What brings you to the embassy today?

Texts.Chs: 您一定去过许多壮丽难言，令人震撼的地方吧。
Texts.Eng: You must have seen some incredible places.
